Great sandwiches every time is what we do. That's not true! I just had the worst experience ever with this location. I wanted to try the new Hero, but they were out of salami. I wanted Italian Herb bread, but they were out. I asked for a cup of water that I get at every location, but they were out of cups. Out of everything on a Tuesday at dinner time is unacceptable. Never mind I'm sitting next to a homeless person hanging out in the dining area without making a purchase. A different homeless person asked me to buy him a sub while I was eating. The reason this has become a homeless hangout is because the employees pay them cash and food to take out the trash! I have spent hundreds of dollars at this location over the last two years for individual meals, party platters for my employees, etc. Tonight, is the last time I come back to this location. It's disgusting, poorly managed and the employees obviously don't care about their customers. I'll take my business elsewhere and tell everyone I come in contact to do the same.
